description: The Yuntai Sky Fall in China has cascaded into controversy after a video posted to social media showed water flowing from a pipe built into the rock face.
title: Famous waterfall in China goes viral after hiker finds pipe supplying it

description: U.K. Prime Minister Rishi Sunak acknowledged that it had been "a mistake" for him to have left the D-Day ceremonies in Normandy early. He has been widely criticized for returning to the U.K. for a TV interview. Britain holds national elections on July 4 and Sunak's ruling Conservatives are trailing in the polls.
title: British PM apologizes for leaving 80th D-Day commemorations early

description: The Philippine coast guard on Friday accused its Chinese counterpart of blocking efforts to evacuate a sick member of its armed forces in the South China Sea.
title: Philippines accuses Chinese coast guard of ‘barbaric’ blocking of medical evacuation

description: The Paris Olympics organizers unveiled a display of the five Olympic rings mounted on the Eiffel Tower, as the French capital marked 50 days until the start of the Summer Games.
title: Olympic rings installed on Eiffel Tower to mark 50 days to start of the Paris Games
